name: Learn How A API works with David Beckhum
about: An API is a piece of software within a system that defines how other components or systems can use that system. The API defines the types of requests that can be made, how to make them, and the data formats that must be used.

name: Learn Microsoft Excel and Complete guideline
about: Microsoft Excel is the industry leading spreadsheet program, used by millions of people all over the world. Excel and other spreadsheet tools are great for data manipulation, analysis, and visualization – you can sort, filter, format, and chart your data all within one program.

name: Learn The Basics of Java Language
about: Java is a general-purpose, class-based, object-oriented programming language designed for having lesser implementation dependencies. It is a computing platform for application development. Java is fast, secure, and reliable, therefore.

name: Develop Native Apps with Kotlin
about: Kotlin is a general purpose, free, open source, statically typed “pragmatic” programming language initially designed for the JVM (Java Virtual Machine) and Android that combines object-oriented and functional programming features. It is focused on interoperability, safety, clarity, and tooling support

name: Learn about competitive Programming Basics
about: Competitive programming is a mind sport usually held over the Internet or a local network, involving participants trying to program according to provided specifications. Contestants are referred to as sport programmers

name: Learn Basics of C programming
about: C is a high-level and general-purpose programming language that is ideal for developing firmware or portable applications. Originally intended for writing system software, C was developed at Bell Labs by Dennis Ritchie for the Unix Operating System in the early 1970s

name: Learn Microsoft Excel With projects
about: Microsoft Excel is a software program produced by Microsoft that allows users to organize, format and calculate data with formulas using a spreadsheet system. This software is part of the Microsoft Office suite and is compatible with other applications in the Office suite.

name: Learn Advanced Adobe Photoshop
about: Photoshop is Adobe's photo editing, image creation and graphic design software. The software provides many image editing features for raster (pixel-based) images as well as vector graphics. It uses a layer-based editing system that enables image creation and altering with multiple overlays that support transparency.

name: Learn Cotext of Flutter From Scratch

name: Learn MongoDB for DataBase Solution
about: MongoDB is an open source NoSQL database management program. NoSQL is used as an alternative to traditional relational databases. NoSQL databases are quite useful for working with large sets of distributed data. MongoDB is a tool that can manage document-oriented information, store or retrieve information.
